    \label{fig:mirage}
\end{figure}

Referring to Fig. \ref{fig:mirage}, we can see how the temperature gradient causes the light rays to bend. As the road heats up, the air just above it becomes warmer and less dense, resulting in a lower refractive index. The light rays from the sky bend towards the denser, cooler air above, eventually reaching a point where they bend upwards, creating the illusion of a water pool on the road.

