Symbolically, $I_3 = R_{23} T_2 R_{12} I_1$.

Let $P_{12} = \frac{1-n}{r_1 n}$ and $P_{23} = \frac{n-1}{r_2}$.

Then

\[
\begin{pmatrix}
l_3 \\
\alpha_3
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
1 & 0 \\
P_{23} & n
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
1 & d \\
0 & 1
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
1 & 0 \\
P_{12} & \frac{1}{n}
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
l_1 \\
\alpha_1
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
1 + d P_{12} & d \\
n P_{23} + d P_{23} P_{12} + n P_{12} & d P_{23} + 1
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
l_1 \\
\alpha_1
\end{pmatrix}
\]

\begin{center}
