The optical path length for the ray emanating from $S_2$ would be $S_2O$. Clearly, $S_1O + (\mu - 1)t > S_2O$. Consequently, the central fringe corresponding to zero path difference is not formed at $O$, the normal position of the central fringe in the absence of the plate. The new position of the central fringe would be at $O'$ such that:

\[
S_1O' + (\mu - 1)t = S_2O'
