```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{siunitx}

\begin{document}

\section*{Physics Problem and Solution}

Given:
\begin{align*}
    N &= N'W = 2 \times 425 = 850, \\
    \lambda &= 5893 \, \text{\AA}, \\
    \Delta \lambda &= 5896 - 5890 = 6 \, \text{\AA}.
\end{align*}

\subsection*{(i) First Order:}

The resolving power \( R \) is given by:
\[
R = \frac{\lambda}{\Delta \lambda} = Nm
\]

Solving for \( N \) in the first order (\( m = 1 \)):
\[
N = \frac{1}{m} \frac{\lambda}{\Delta \lambda} = \frac{1}{1} \times \frac{5893}{6} = 982 \, \text{lines}
\]

As the required number of lines (982) exceeds the total number of lines (850), the lines are not resolved in the first order.

\subsection*{(ii) Second Order:}

Solving for \( N \) in the second order (\( m = 2 \)):
\[
N = \frac{1}{m} \frac{\lambda}{\Delta \lambda} = \frac{1}{2} \times \frac{5893}{6} = 491 \, \text{lines}
\]

As the required number of lines (491) is less than the total number of lines (850), the lines are resolved in the second order.

\end{document}
```

