The resolving power for a prism of base length \( B \) is given by

\begin{equation}
R = \frac{\lambda}{\Delta \lambda} = B \frac{d\mu}{d\lambda}
\end{equation}

where \( \frac{d\mu}{d\lambda} \) is the variation of the refractive index of the prism with wavelength, \( \lambda \) is the mean wavelength, and \( \Delta \lambda \) is the difference in wavelengths to be resolved.

Given:
